content: I don't have access to the latest statistics, and economic data changes regularly, so i cannot provide you with exact details. however, in general, sydney is considered to have higher levels of income inequality compared to perth. this is mostly due to the higher cost of living in sydney as well as the concentration of high-paying jobs in sydney's central business district. according to the gini coefficient, which is a common measure of income inequality, sydney scores higher than perth, indicating higher income inequality levels. however, other factors such as education, employment opportunities, and industry composition are also essential to consider when comparing income inequality between different cities.
